# Demo move — drive the arm to a fixed joint-space pose and open
# the gripper to a wide neutral width. Used for canned showcase
# runs where the operator wants every "pick" gesture to land at the
# same hard-coded configuration regardless of perception output.
#
# Schema mirrors Reset.srv exactly:
#   * Request has a single bool `ack` so the codegen dataclass has
#     at least one field (FastMCP / codegen routers don't like
#     fully-empty messages).
#   * Response carries success / message / elapsed_s, same shape as
#     Reset_Response, so callers can treat reset and demo
#     interchangeably from a control-flow standpoint.
#
# Internally this calls the cpp's /moveit_control/demo
# (std_srvs/srv/Trigger) ROS service. Gripper width is configured
# inside the cpp node via the `demo_gripper_width` ros param
# (default 0.08 m = 8 cm jaw gap), NOT through this MCP IDL —
# that keeps the contract minimal and lets the operator tweak
# demo behaviour without re-codegenning.

# Request
bool ack
---
# Response
bool   success
string message
float32 elapsed_s
